Run a package executable

USAGE:
    ir tool run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] --from <pkg-ref> <command> [args...]
    ir tool run [Rscript-options...] [--with <pkg>]... [--r-version <spec>] <pkg-ref> [args...]

`ir tool run` resolves <pkg-ref>, finds <library>/<package>/exec/<command>
or <command>.R, and launches it with the selected Rscript. A bare package
ref such as `btw` is treated as `--from btw btw`. Tool runs are isolated:
R_LIBS_USER is set to NULL so undeclared user-library packages are not
borrowed.

OPTIONS:
    --from <pkg-ref>
                  Resolve a package ref and run <command> from its exec/
                  directory. Omit for self-named commands such as `btw`.
    --with <pkg>  Add a dependency for this run, resolved alongside the
                  provider package. May be repeated and accepts a
                  comma-separated list (e.g. --with cli,jsonlite).
    --r-version <spec>
                  Select the R version for this tool run with rig.

ENVIRONMENT:
    IR_CACHE_DIR   override the cache dir (default: tools::R_user_dir("ir", "cache"))
    IR_RSCRIPT     path to the Rscript executable (default: Rscript on PATH)
